		"notes": [
			{
				"category": "summary",
				"text": "Security update for gdm",
				"title": "Title of the patch"
			},
			{
				"category": "description",
				"text": "This update for gdm fixes the following issues:\n\nSecurity issue fixed:\n\n- CVE-2019-3825: Fixed a lock screen bypass when timed login was enabled (bsc#1124628).\n\nOther issues fixed:\n\n- GLX applications do not work well when the proprietary nvidia driver is used with a\n  wayland session. Because of that this update disables wayland on that hardware (bsc#1112578).\n- Fixed an issue where gdm restart fails to kill user processes (bsc#1112294 and bsc#1113245).\n- Fixed a System halt in the screen with message 'End of ORACLE section' (bsc#1120307).\n- Fixed an issue which did not allow the returning to text console when gdm is stopped (bsc#1113700).\t\n- Fixed an issue which was causing system hang during the load of gdm (bsc#1112578).\n\nThis update was imported from the SUSE:SLE-15:Update update project.",
				"title": "Description of the patch"
			},
			{
				"category": "details",
				"text": "openSUSE-2019-310",
				"title": "Patchnames"
			},
